## Architecture

### Agent graph

```
diagram_coordinator  (root_agent — LlmAgent, multimodal)
│
├── tools:
│     AgentTool(image_extractor)   ← coordinator calls this; summary returns into context
│     list_diagrams()              ← ADK tool for "show my diagrams" queries
│
└── sub_agents (coordinator transfers to one of these):
      drawio_generator             LoopAgent(max_iterations=3)
        drawio_writer              LlmAgent, output_key="diagram_code"
        DiagramValidator("drawio") BaseAgent — validate only, no DB write
      mermaid_sequence_generator   LoopAgent(max_iterations=3)
        mermaid_sequence_writer    LlmAgent, output_key="diagram_code"
        DiagramValidator("mermaid_sequence")
      mermaid_flowchart_generator  LoopAgent(max_iterations=3)
        mermaid_flowchart_writer   LlmAgent, output_key="diagram_code"
        DiagramValidator("mermaid_flowchart")
```

### Request flow (API path)

```
POST /diagrams
  → create_job() → jobs collection (status: pending)
  → BackgroundTasks.add_task(_process_job)
  ← 202 { job_id }   (returns immediately)

_process_job() [background]
  → set_running(job_id)
  → run_request(text, image_bytes?, image_mime?, requested_format?)
      → ADK Runner runs diagram_coordinator
          → if image: call image_extractor tool → image_summary into state
          → coordinator transfers to correct generator LoopAgent
              → writer LlmAgent generates code → diagram_code into state
              → DiagramValidator checks code
                  → valid: sets final_format in state, escalates (loop stops)
                  → invalid: sets validation_feedback in state (loop retries writer, max 3×)
      ← agent run completes
      → runner reads final_format + diagram_code from session state
      → runner calls persist_diagram() → diagrams collection
      ← returns { status, format, code, mongo_id }
  → set_done(job_id, result)  OR  set_failed(job_id, error)
  → if callback_url: POST result to caller

GET /diagrams/{job_id}
  ← { id, status, result: {format, code, mongo_id} | null, error | null, created_at, updated_at }
```

### Key separation of concerns

- **Agent layer** — generation and validation only. Zero MongoDB imports. Zero HTTP imports.
- **API layer (`runner.py`)** — owns all persistence. After the agent returns, `runner.py` calls `persist_diagram()`. This is the only place diagrams are written to MongoDB.
- `DiagramValidator` — deterministic Python validator. On success: sets `final_format` in session state, escalates (stops the loop). On failure: writes error list to `validation_feedback` in state and yields an event (no escalate — loop retries).

