## Validation Rules

### `validate_drawio(code) -> (bool, list[str])`
- Parse with `defusedxml.ElementTree.fromstring` (not stdlib — XXE/billion-laughs risk).
- Strip markdown fences (` ```xml `, ` ```drawio `, ` ``` `) before parsing.
- Assert `<mxGraphModel>` exists anywhere in the tree (DFS).
- Assert `<mxGraphModel>` has a `<root>` child.
- Assert `<root>` contains at least 2 `<mxCell>` elements (the two default parent cells `id=0`, `id=1` are always required).
- Collect all failures; return `(False, errors)` on any failure.

### `validate_mermaid(code, kind) -> (bool, list[str])`
No pure-Python Mermaid grammar parser exists. Uses heuristics:
- Strip markdown fences (` ```mermaid `, ` ``` `).
- Non-empty after stripping comments (`%%`) and whitespace.
- First significant line matches expected header:
  - `mermaid_sequence` → `sequenceDiagram` (case-insensitive)
  - `mermaid_flowchart` → `flowchart TD|TB|BT|LR|RL` or `graph TD|...`
- At least one arrow/edge in the body:
  - sequence: `-->>`, `->`, `->>`, `-->`, `->>`
  - flowchart: `-->`, `---`, `-.->`, `===>`, `===`
- Balanced `()`, `[]`, `{}` (ignoring content inside string literals `"..."` / `'...'`).

**Upgrade seam:** `validate_mermaid`'s body can be replaced with a Node `mermaid.parse` call or a self-hosted Kroki HTTP check without changing the `DiagramValidator` or LoopAgent.

