## MongoDB Schema

### Collection: `diagrams` (env: `MONGODB_COLLECTION`)
Holds successfully validated and persisted diagrams. Written by `runner.py` via `persist_diagram()`.

```json
{
  "_id": ObjectId,
  "title": "string (first 120 chars of the request text)",
  "format": "drawio | mermaid_sequence | mermaid_flowchart",
  "code": "string (full diagram source)",
  "source": "image | text",
  "session_id": "string",
  "created_at": ISODate
}
```

### Collection: `jobs`
Tracks fire-and-forget API job lifecycle. Written by `api/jobs.py`.

```json
{
  "_id": ObjectId,
  "status": "pending | running | done | failed",
  "request": {
    "text": "string",
    "format": "drawio | mermaid_sequence | mermaid_flowchart | null",
    "image_mime": "image/png | ... | null",
    "callback_url": "string | null"
  },
  "result": {
    "status": "done",
    "format": "string",
    "code": "string",
    "mongo_id": "string"
  },
  "error": "string | null",
  "created_at": ISODate,
  "updated_at": ISODate
}
```

Note: `image_base64` is intentionally **not** stored in the job doc (can be large); it is passed in memory during background processing only.

