## REST API Contract

### `POST /diagrams`
Submit a diagram generation job. Returns immediately.

**Request body:**
```json
{
  "text": "required — description of the diagram",
  "image_base64": "optional — base64-encoded image (PNG, JPEG, GIF, WEBP)",
  "image_mime": "optional — required when image_base64 is set, e.g. 'image/png'",
  "format": "optional — 'drawio' | 'mermaid_sequence' | 'mermaid_flowchart'",
  "callback_url": "optional — URL to POST result to on completion"
}
```

**Response: `202 Accepted`**
```json
{ "job_id": "string", "status": "pending" }
```

### `GET /diagrams/{job_id}`
Poll for job status and result.

**Response:**
```json
{
  "id": "string",
  "status": "pending | running | done | failed",
  "result": { "format": "...", "code": "...", "mongo_id": "..." },
  "error": "string | null",
  "created_at": "ISO8601",
  "updated_at": "ISO8601"
}
```

### `GET /healthz`
Pings MongoDB. Returns `200 { "status": "ok", "mongodb": "reachable" }` or `503` if MongoDB is unreachable.

### Callback payload (when `callback_url` is provided)
```json
{
  "job_id": "string",
  "status": "done | failed",
  "result": { "format": "...", "code": "...", "mongo_id": "..." },
  "error": "string | null"
}
```
Callback failures are silently ignored — they must not affect job state.

