## Agent Instructions Summary

Each prompt lives in `diagram_agent/prompts/<name>.py` as a module-level `INSTRUCTION` string.

| Agent | Key instruction points |
|---|---|
| `coordinator` | Routing rules (image → extractor → drawio default or explicit override; no image → named format or ask). Never generate diagrams itself. |
| `image_extractor` | Output a structured summary: diagram type, direction, nodes (id/label/shape), edges (from/to/label/style), groups, annotations. Factual only — no business interpretation. |
| `drawio_writer` | Must output complete `<mxfile>` XML in a ` ```xml ` fence. Must always include the two default `mxCell` (id=0, id=1). Must read `{validation_feedback?}` and fix exactly those issues on retry. |
| `mermaid_sequence_writer` | First line must be exactly `sequenceDiagram`. Must read `{validation_feedback?}` on retry. Syntax reference included in prompt. |
| `mermaid_flowchart_writer` | First line must be `flowchart TD` (or LR/BT/RL). Must read `{validation_feedback?}` on retry. Syntax reference + node shapes included in prompt. |

All writer prompts reference two optional state variables:
- `{image_summary?}` — present when the request included an image
- `{validation_feedback?}` — present when a previous attempt failed validation

